The county speakers forum was today raising alarm over the rising incidents of impeachment of speakers by members of county assemblies  across the country. The forum has now proposed the enactment of procedures which will require the approval of the senate before a speaker is impeached to tame the runway wrangles in the assemblies. And as Rose Gakuo reports the proposal was floated as speakers from Nyandarua and Homa Bay counties faced the wrath of  disgruntled ward representatives.  